mary: Build leave-web-app React Frontend\n\n## Issue Overview\n**Title:** Build leave-web-app React frontend #3  \n**Status:** Open  \n**Labels:** asdlc, implementation, pending  \n**Created:** April 24, 2026\n\n## Component Details\n- **Name:** leave-web-app\n- **Type:** Web application\n- **Technology Stack:** TypeScript / React\n- **Location:** `/leave-web-app`\n- **Port:** 8080\n\n## Key Responsibilities\nThe application must deliver:\n- Employee dashboard displaying leave balance by type\n- Leave request submission form (start date, end date, leave type)\n- Request status tracking (pending, approved, rejected)\n- Pending request cancellation capability\n- Manager dashboard for reviewing direct reports' requests\n- Approval/rejection functionality with optional comments\n- User authentication with role-based rendering\n- RESTful integration with leave-api and manager-api\n- Express server serving static assets\n- Health monitoring endpoint\n\n## API Dependencies\nTwo critical service integrations required:\n\n1. **leave-api** → `LEAVE_API_URL` environment variable\n2. **manager-api** → `MANAGER_API_URL` environment variable\n\n## Technical Requirements\n- TypeScript for type safety\n- React Router for navigation\n- Client-side validation before API calls\n- React Context for user state management\n- Multi-stage Docker build (Node 18 → Node 18-Alpine)\n- Environment variable configuration for API endpoints\n\n## Working Directory\n```\n/Users/kajendran/.asdlc/repos/default/kaj-test-18/leave-web-app\n```\n\nAll implementation files must remain within this directory.","durationMs":5765,"url":"https://github.com/asdlc-repos/kaj-test-18041/issues/3"}}
